-- Wells Fargo Adds Shapiro as Kinross Hires Gill, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-07-19T18:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-19/wells-fargo-adds-shapiro-as-kinross-hires-gill-vlaad-says.html
Wells Fargo & Co. (WFC)  added Stephen
Shapiro as a managing director from BMO Capital Markets, where
he was managing director and head of the agriculture and
fertilizer group, according to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based
financial-services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * BMO promoted Jim Fitzgerald to vice chairman focusing on U.S.-
based fixed-income sales and to help expand the U.S. platform.  * Brad Rothbaum was named managing director and head of U.S.
trading products business oversight at BMO. Rothbaum continues
as chief operating officer and general manager of the BMO  New
York  Branch.  * In the U.K., RBC Capital Markets hired Darrell Uden as head of
European equity capital markets from UBS AG.  * In Calgary, Desjardins Securities brought on Justin Bouchard
and Kristopher Zack as co-heads of energy research from Raymond
James.  * Rajbir Gill moved to  Kinross Gold Corp. (K)  as a corporate
development manager from Cormark Securities Inc. where he was a
research associate, base metals and bulk commodities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
